com.moandjiezana.uncommons.dbutils

Interface ResultSetHandler<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the target type the input ResultSet will be converted to.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MapResultSetHandler
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ResultSetHandler<T>
    Converts ResultSets to other objects.

      • handle

        T handle(ResultSet rs)
  throws Exception
        Turn the ResultSet into an instance of T.
        Parameters:
        rs - The ResultSet to handle. It has not been touched before being passed to this method.
        Returns:
        An Object initialized with ResultSet data. Implementations may return null.
        Throws:
        Exception - if a database access error occurs
